sentences: Momo Kodama (児玉 桃, Kodama Momo, born 1972) is a Japanese classical pianist.
She made her debut in 1991 with the Berkeley Symphony Orchestra and was the youngest winner of the International Piano Competition in Munich at age 19.
Kodama was born in Osaka, Japan, but spent her early years in Europe, with her family moving there in 1973 and attending school in Germany.
